. <p>

He is a founding co-President of the <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://www.bayesian.org/">
International Society for Bayesian Analysis (ISBA), 1992-1994</weblink>. His areas of research interest are: 
<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

The nature and scope of Bayesian Statistics</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

The relationship between information theory and statistics </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

The foundations and the derivation of nonsubjective, reference priors</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

The foundations of decision theory </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Bayesian hypothesis testing and model criticism</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Point and region intrinsic estimation</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Probabilistic classification</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Applications of Bayesian Statistics and decision theory to medical problems (automatic diagnosis)</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Political analysis (election forecasting, sample surveys), </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Industrial problems (quality assurance).</entry>
</list>
</p>

